place.name: WEEKE
place.gazetteerText: WEEKE, a parish in Winchester district, Hants; partly within W. city, and containing W. r. station and W. workhouse. Post town, Winchester. Acres, 1,080. Real property, £4,099. Pop. in 1861, 529; of whom 137 were in the workhouse. Houses, 88. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £234. Patron, the Bishop of W. The church is Norman. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
